National Experience with Living Donor Liver Transplantation (LDLT) for Hepatocellular Carcinoma (HCC).
5-year post-LT survival (LDLT 77% vs DDLT 75%), graft survival (72% vs 72%) and HCC recurrence (11% vs 13%) were similar between groups (all p>0.20). In conclusion, LDLT utilization for HCC has remained low since 2002 with only a slight increase after the 6-month wait policy introduction in 2015. Given excellent post-LT survival, LDLT appears to be an underutilized but valuable option for HCC patients, especially those at high-risk for waitlist dropout.
