    Chronic Jetlag Alters the Landscape of the Pancreatic Lipidome.
The pancreatic lipidome exhibits diurnal rhythmicity across a broad number of lipid classes. Chronic jetlag led to alterations in lipid composition that mirrored other metabolically active organs. Several of the reported changes may link altered sleep-wake cycles with known circadian disruption-induced pancreatic diseases.
